1) Command to create  group :

                   sudo groupadd  Devops  --
                                       

2 ) Create user  :
                   sudo adduser username
                   ex: sudo adduser vikas

3) adding user to group
       usermod -a -G groupname username

        add an existing user to an existing group on Linux, you commonly use the usermod command with the -a (append) and -G options:


how to check the number of user and group
          1)  To count how many users are there:
                 cat /etc/passwd | wc -l
          2)  To count how many groups are there:                //wc -l in Linux is used to count the number of lines in a file or input.
                   cat /etc/group | wc -l
